<dl id="n54109h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54109h">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54109h"> 109(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Ansar helper <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n54109h"><li>FW 5.25 </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/lexa.htm#n54109h">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/a/l39a.htm#n54109h">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n54109h">MS BL 47476a-135</ms> </li><li>JJA 49:293 <a name="ad7" href="../../FF/fdra/ada.htm#ad7">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/a/ad7.htm#n54109h">Draft: I.1&sect;1.7</a>/2.7</li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">There were many exiles from Meccah, who had fled from the persecutions of the Kuraysh; they were known as the Muhajirin or Refugees, while the citizen of Med&#299;nah, who were converts, were called <mark>Ansars, or Helpers</mark>. <small> Edith Holland, <a name="EHSM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EHSM"><cite title="source">The Story of Mohammed</cite></a> (1914) 91</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
